HEADWORD: Rimmer
<hw>Rim"mer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An implement for
cutting, trimming, or ornamenting the rim of anything, as the edges of
pies, etc.; also, a reamer.</def> <rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

